Ingredients:400g (2 cups) sugar30ml (2 tbsp) oil30ml (2 tbsp) fresh cream125ml ( cup) white poppy seeds15ml (1 tbsp) sesame seeds2.5ml ( tsp) ground cardamomMethod:1) Heat sugar and oil in a small, heavy-based pan, stirring until the sugar is dissolved. Continue to cook on a moderate heat without stirring until the sugar turns amber.2) Remove from the heat and add the cream - be careful; it will splatter.3) Add the seeds and cardamom and mix into the syrup. Quickly pour onto a marble slab or greaseproof paper to cool.4) Break up the brittle when cold and store in an airtight container.Cook s tip:For a nutty flavour, add a couple of nibbed almonds with the seeds.